 aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104anr1665702755836.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/anr1665702755836.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/anr1665702755836.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"anr1665702755836\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface Mobile Apps\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"anr1665702755836__uniface_mobile_apps_91311\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Uniface mobile app is essentially a wrapped web application, so it consists of a hybrid mobile app that provides the client-side user interface and functionality, and a Uniface runtime environment that executes server-side components and reads and writes data in a database.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"anr1665702755836__p_d27728e1_d27729e1_d27730e1\">This type of architecture is commonly know as a <dfn class=\"term\">packaged hybrid app</dfn>. It enables you to develop the same code for all platforms, but take advantage of native functionality.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The client consists of a wrapper around a web-based user interface provided by dynamic server\n      page (DSP) components. The app can access the device functions it needs (such as camera and\n      geolocation) via JavaScript APIs provided by plug-ins.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"anr1665702755836__p_d27731e1_d27732e1_d27733e1\">The wrapper is generated by a hybrid app framework, which enables you to specify the target mobile platforms, the plug-ins required to access device features, as well as the initial web page to be displayed.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"anr1665702755836__fig_d27734e1_d27735e1_d27736e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Uniface Mobile App Architecture</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Runtime architecture of a Uniface mobile app\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/mobileruntimearch.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"anr1665702755836__p_d27740e1_d27741e1_d27742e1\">Because Uniface mobile apps are wrapped web applications, they share the same infrastructure and communication as web applications. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qpy1665702532414.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qpy1665702532414.html\" title=\"At runtime, dynamic server pages are split into a non-persistent server layer that generates HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and a client layer that handles user input and synchronisation with the server layer. Communication between the client and server layers is asynchronous, via HTTP requests and responses over the internet.\">Client-Server Communication in DSPs</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"anr1665702755836__p_d27743e1_d27744e1_d27745e1\">DSPs for mobile apps make use of a layout framework that\n      controls how content, menus, and navigation tools are defined for rendering on multiple\n      devices, and a mechanism for binding these to DSP components. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wun1665702755914.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wun1665702755914.html\" title=\"Each mobile platform has its own user interface and interaction conventions, which affect the layout of a mobile application. The Mobile App Layout is a framework that maps HTML elements in a DSP layout to generic layout definitions.\">Mobile App Layout</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"anr1665702755836__p_d27746e1_d27747e1_d27748e1\">To run the web server side of the mobile application, you can define a customized application server for the mobile app backend. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kcv1665702756074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kcv1665702756074.html\" title=\"A server shell defines the behavior of an application server, which is responsible for executing remote components such as server pages and services.\">Application Shells for Servers</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unv1665702768403.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Developing a Mobile App</a><p>Uniface's mobile solution is based on web technologies, so mobile development starts with creating a responsive web application that is tailored to the possibilities and limitations of mobile devices.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Mobile Apps Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Mobile Apps A Uniface mobile app is essentially a wrapped web application, so it consists of a hybrid mobile app that provides the client-side user interface and functionality, and a Uniface runtime environment that executes server-side components and reads and writes data in a database. This type of architecture is commonly know as a packaged hybrid app . It enables you to develop the same code for all platforms, but take advantage of native functionality. The client consists of a wrapper around a web-based user interface provided by dynamic server page (DSP) components. The app can access the device functions it needs (such as camera and geolocation) via JavaScript APIs provided by plug-ins. The wrapper is generated by a hybrid app framework, which enables you to specify the target mobile platforms, the plug-ins required to access device features, as well as the initial web page to be displayed. Figure 1. Uniface Mobile App Architecture Because Uniface mobile apps are wrapped web applications, they share the same infrastructure and communication as web applications. For more information, see Client-Server Communication in DSPs . DSPs for mobile apps make use of a layout framework that controls how content, menus, and navigation tools are defined for rendering on multiple devices, and a mechanism for binding these to DSP components. For more information, see Mobile App Layout . To run the web server side of the mobile application, you can define a customized application server for the mobile app backend. For more information, see Application Shells for Servers . Related Links Developing a Mobile App Uniface's mobile solution is based on web technologies, so mobile development starts with creating a responsive web application that is tailored to the possibilities and limitations of mobile devices. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}